Here is a very cool Squier "Custom Shack Surf Green Tele" with some very nice upgrades. The Squier maple/rosewood neck has near zero fret wear ,and has had a nice headstock make over with many coats of cleat over the decal. The Body looks very nice, only mild surface scratches. Guitar features Texas Special pickups,9.3k-neck,10.3k-bridge. All of the pickup cavities and control cavities have been lined with copper foil to control noise. The pots are CTS with a CRL type three way switch,all cloth covered wiring. All electronics work perfectly,and sound great on every setting,clean or with some distortion. The capacitor has been upgraded with a .022 epoxy film capacitor . More range of tone control and a smoother response. Action is great and this guitar wails. Comes with a nice lightly used hardshell case with key. This guitar sounds really good,and it looks like a classic. This "Custom Shack" came out great!!!
